---
title: Tex-Mex Plant-Based Protein Taco Soup Protein that tastes like meat (without the meat)
description: A soup that tastes like tacos but is even easier to make (and it’s vegetarian)? It’s not just a culinary fantasy—this hearty, zesty pot of goodness is the real deal! Tex-Mex-seasoned ground plant-based protein is browned along with jalapeño and scallion whites, then simmered with black beans in a flavorful vegetable broth. Just like tacos, each bowl is finished with your favorite fixings: a sprinkle of Mexican cheese, crisp jalapeño slices, a bright flurry of scallion greens, plus blue corn tortilla chips for dipping or crumbling on top. Grab your big spoon for this one, folks!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/652e9bf50adad327d2408d8c-dddf153d.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/652e9bf50adad327d2408d8c.pdf
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 720 kcal
  fat: 37 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 64 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 35 g
  fiber: 12 g
  sodium: 1640 mg
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/tex-mex-plant-based-protein-taco-soup-652e9bf50adad327d2408d8c
time required: 20 minutes
cuisine: North America
---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2%unit}, separating whites from greens. Halve @jalapeño{1%unit} lengthwise, removing ribs and seeds for less heat; thinly slice half the jalapeño into half-moons and dice remaining jalapeño.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and diced jalapeño; cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @Tex-Mex ground plant-based protein{8%oz} and press into an even layer with a #spatula{}; cook, undisturbed, until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add @black beans{1%unit} and their liquid, @veggie stock concentrate{1%unit}, and 2 cups water (4 cups for 4 servings). Cook, stirring occasionally and scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pot, until soup has thickened, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Taste and season with a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide soup between #bowls{}. Top with @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup} and as much sliced jalapeño as you like. Sprinkle with scallion greens and serve with @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%oz} on the side.

> Plant-based protein is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165º.